profile_summary.text: Ebrahim Jahanshiri is a highly experienced practitioner in predictive statistical modeling, machine learning, deep learning, LLM fine-tuning and RAG solutions, MLOps, data management, cloud computation, GIS, remote sensing, and geospatial analytics. With 15 years of experience, he has built large-scale data and AI systems, pioneered big-data analytics in agriculture, improved revenue through European projects, and communicated complex insights to influence business decisions.

skills.text: Python, R, SQL, TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn, Spark, Hadoop, GIS, Remote Sensing, Google Earth Engine, AWS, GCP, Data Warehousing, DVC, MLflow, Airflow, Git, Tableau, Power BI.

education.text: MSc in Applied Data Science, University of Gothenburg & Chalmers University of Technology. PhD in GIS and Geomatics Engineering, Universiti Putra Malaysia. MSc in Precision Farming, Universiti Putra Malaysia. B.S. in Agricultural Engineering, Ferdowsi University of Mashhad.

experience.text: Over 15 years of experience across roles such as Data Science Manager, Geospatial Data Scientist, Data Manager, and AI/ML Engineer. Led major European Commission AI and geospatial projects, developed cloud-based data portals (GCP, AWS), built predictive models, fine-tuned LLMs, managed teams up to 24 members, and contributed to high-impact agricultural, climate, sustainability, NLP, and medical AI projects.
